data.title: Lunch
data.text: I had a Reuben, and a cup of the daily soup ... Today's was sausage chicken gumbo. That was some of the best gumbo I've ever had. The sandwich was great, too. I highly recommend stopping here for a great lunch!

data.title: Coming back!!
data.text: Had to come look for this deli in a sea of Mexican food restaurants and it was so worth it.  Close resemblance to a New York style deli (for south Texas), Beatles Fans, you will get your fill for the day.  Great quality food, all Bore's Head products.  They are proud of what they serve and it shows.  Everything looks so good I have to come back for more.  You have to stop here if your in Harlingen.

data.title: Lovely.  Historic.  Go here.
data.text: If you would like to share a really nice experience with a friend or family, I recommend the New York Deli.  The atmosphere is the nicest in my opinion, in Harlingen.  And, it is just a short walk down to Grimsell's Nursery.  A nice combination that cannot be beat.

data.title: Downtown Harlingen's hidden treasure
data.text: If you are in the mood for a freshly prepared hamburger and fries or perhaps your would prefer a grilled chicken sandwich, then you need to head to New York Deli. You can order any of their many delicious sandwiches with a number of different combinations of toppings and sides. All meals are guaranteed to be tasty and made to order. I have never had a bad experience and I love all of the Beatles memorabilia on the walls. The staff are excellent and take care of you.

data.title: Best Deli in South Texas
data.text: Groovy atmosphere and excellent food. Hard to find a deli that can compare. Fresh cuts of meat.. delish salads and soups. Great service.

data.title: get the bean soup. period.
data.text:
clean, downhome décor, gr8 variety on the menu.
the pastrami is fantastic, but you have to get the bean soup.....wow......so good.

data.title: Downtown dining in Harlingen
data.text: Eclectic and Beatle mania décor. Nothing to write home about. But the sandwiches are great and the service wonderful. No box store or chain brand here. Love that it is quiet and yet a lively friendly place.

data.title: meatloaf mania
data.text: Great lace for lunch when you are in Harlingen.  The service is fast, friendly and correct at this family owned restaurant.  Make sure you are hungry because the portion are large and tasty.  Try the German meatloaf, you will not be disappointed.

data.title: Best Reuben anywhere!!
data.text: I try Reuben's everywhere I go. I live in Harlingen and the NY deli is the best anywhere. Also best navy beans, Cole slaw and potato salad. Several of us eat there and I have never had anyone not like their meal.

data.title: Excellent Deli sandwiches....
data.text: Great deli to eat & a great atmosphere with all the Beatle pictures!!!  A very handy location on Monroe Street just off Commerce in downtown Harlingen. Lots of parking and the staff is quick to sit you.  We arrived with a dozen Winter Texans from Sunshine RV Resort and were welcomed by a friendly waiter who quickly took us to our seats and layed out the menu's.  There is every type of deli sandwich that you can think of and the choices we made were all excellent.  Once the food arrived the waiter took our picture and downloaded it onto their Facebook page. There is not a license to sell booze but you are allowed to bring in your own bottle of wine or beer.  Very reasonable prices and very clean too!!  We've enjoyed going back there twice!!

data.title: Great food, friendly service!
data.text: I've been a New York Deli fan for a long time.  I've never been disappointed!  Ever!  Come hungry, the portions are large!  The Manhattan is my favorite sandwich, the salads, the soup and chili are all great.  Everything I've tried has been delicious!  The owners/managers are friendly and know the regulars by first name.

data.title: Good Coney Island Dog!
data.text: Good Deli Style food, great sandwiches, excellent soups.  Like the Beatlemania Decor, fun. Good place for lunch, I always enjoy their food.

data.title: Consistently Great Sandwiches!
data.text: We have been regulars at this deli since they opened in Harlingen in a different location. This is the only place to get a traditional Reuben sandwich: corned beef grilled on rye bread with saurkraut, Swiss cheese, and Russian dressing. Another of my favorites is their patty melt, though I get it with only Swiss, and I recommend specifying that it be cooked medium. They have great homemade fries, also. Their sides of cole slaw and potato salad and very good, though some might find them small. They used to have a beer license, but they let it lapse. If you want a brew with your sandwich, just bring your favorite!

data.title: Great sandwiches!
data.text: The Manhattan is my favorite, but there are many others to choose from.  Good service and interesting décor.

data.title: Navy bean soup, real fries, it's all good!
data.text: Just a great option for lunch in Harlingen. Burgers, hot dogs, sandwiches, etc. Please get the navy beans soup as a side... or the fries ;)

data.title: #1 Deli in the Valley!
data.text: New York Deli 2 in Harlingen is my all-time favorite deli anywhere! It is my go to place to meet friends for lunch. It is also the place I order "to go" from when I'm feeling under the weather. Their homemade chicken soup will cure what ails ya! I have not ordered anything that I didn't like! They are famous for their Reuben sandwiches, but, my favorite, hands down, is the #6 on the lunch specials menu: ham and cheese (I like it hot). Lunch specials are served with soup, and your choice of chips, cole slaw, or the best potato salad you've ever tasted! Another good choice is the Manhattan, served with Russian dressing. They have been the "Reader's Choice" Award Winner multiple years for their french fries. The owner and wait staff have been together for many years, and all are very cordial and welcoming.

data.title: Found a hair, that was way to black  to be mine
data.text:
Food is average.
I found a hair, and asked for the manager, I was told she was busy, so after waiting a few minutes I got up went over to the front counter and when telling the manager, she said"I know who this belongs to" she went in back and I never saw her again. We paid and left and will never go back

data.title: Lunch - Every Day
data.text: This was convenient and the food was really excellent.  They have an extensive lunch sandwich menu - so you don't have to repeat.  The quality of the food was excellent and the service was friendly and efficient.

data.title: We enjoyed it two days in a row
data.text:
If you're wondering where the grilled onion rolls, sourdough and french bread, special sauces, grilled onions, jalapeño and provolone cheeses, sliced avocados, croissants (!!), specialty mustards, and good deli meats have all gone to, they're waiting for you at NY Deli.  We enjoyed this Beatles-themed restaurant so much, we went a second day.  And the week isn't over yet!

I have to say that although their reuben sandwich was decent, it was far from the best I've had.  But for this part of Texas, it probably deserves the high ratings that other reviewers have given it.   Their kingston and manhattan sandwiches and Sergeant Pepper burger more than made up for it.  They were gourmet.  The meals came with a nice dill pickle, a carrot sliver, and a side dish.  We had fries, cole slaw, and potato salad and all were good.  Of the four dishes we ordered, the burger and kingston sandwich were the best.

The wait staff were very good and helpful with suggestions and customer favorites.  Service was fast too, both days.  On day two, the place was full and we had our meal delivered in about 8 minutes.   Prices were good too at less than $10 each.  We didn't order desert but the carrot and chocolate cakes, half moon cookies, and other items looked fresh.

If this restaurant was located in an east coast city, I'd have given it a 4 rating.  But this is by far the best sandwich place we've eaten in our month of Gulf coast travel, so I rated it as 5.

I hope you enjoy your visit as much as we did.
